  "body": "### Problem\r\n`StatusModal` should be reworked completely. It's wrong to put header and footer in the background item as is done now, because of the implications:\r\n\r\n1) broken content padding - clients can't set padding in a convenient way\r\n```\r\n    StatusModal {\r\n        header.title: \"Random dialog\"\r\n        topPadding: 16 // it should be top padding of the content\r\n\r\n        Text {\r\n            anchors.fill: parent\r\n            text: \"Header makes me invisible\"\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n```\r\n\r\n2) some artificial and strange properties required, like: `advancedHeaderComponent`, `advancedFooterComponent`\r\n```\r\n    StatusModal {\r\n        showFooter: false\r\n        showAdvancedFooter: true\r\n        advancedFooterComponent: CustomFooter {}\r\n    }\r\n```\r\nshould simply be:\r\n```\r\n    StatusModal {\r\n        footer: CustomFooter {}\r\n    }\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\nQt's [Dialog](https://doc.qt.io/qt-5/qml-qtquick-controls2-dialog.html) component should be used as the base component. It already handles/exposes header and footer in a proper way.\r\n\r\n### Acceptance criteria:\r\n- [x] status-im/StatusQ#725\r\n- [ ] introduce `StatusPopup` which derives from Qt [Popup](https://doc.qt.io/qt-5/qml-qtquick-controls2-popup.html)\r\n- [x] status-im/status-desktop#7553\r\n- [ ] use `StatusPopup` in contexts where no \"dialog\" is required\r\n- [ ] remove `StatusModal`\r\n",
